properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued January 31 at 1:27PM MST until February 1 at 12:00PM MST by NWS Riverton WY
properties.description:
...High Wind Warning and Watches across portions of northern and
central Wyoming Tonight through Saturday Night...

.Strong winds aloft and a tight pressure gradient will combine for
high winds across the Cody Foothills and Absaroka Mountains
tonight into Saturday. The strong winds will last across the
Absaroka Mountains through Saturday night. A tight pressure
gradient will also result in strong to possibly high wind across
southeast Fremont into Natrona County Saturday and Saturday night.

* WHAT...West winds 30 to 40 mph with gusts up to 60 mph. Gusts up
to 70 mph could occur around Clark along Highway 120.

* WHERE...Cody Foothills. The strongest winds will occur just
south of Cody, as well as between Clark and the junction of
Highway 120 and the Chief Joseph Highway.

* WHEN...Until noon Saturday. The strongest winds are expected to
occur between 3 AM and 9 AM Saturday.

* IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. An enhanced blow over risk
for light and high profile vehicles including camper trailers
and semi trucks.
properties.instruction:
Use caution if traveling. Please keep two hands on your steering
wheel in case of a sudden, strong wind gust. In a parking lot,
park into the wind to minimize the possibility of your car door
hitting another parked vehicle.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT UNTIL NOON MST SATURDAY
